"1129","1085":"1085","1060":"1060","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Kirby Knowle, Yorkshire, England":"Kirby Knowle, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Matilda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Old German: Mighty battle maid"]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda was born in 1060, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Geoffrey de Lascelles. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1060–":"1060–Surnud","1060–Male":"1060–Surnud","1085–1129":"1085–1129","1060–Female":"1060–Surnud","1129":"1129","1085":"1085","1060":"1060","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kirby Knowle, Yorkshire, England":"Kirby Knowle, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1060–":"1060–Kuollut","1060–Male":"1060–Kuollut","1085–1129":"1085–1129","1060–Female":"1060–Kuollut","1129":"1129","1085":"1085","1060":"1060","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kirby Knowle, Yorkshire, England":"Kirby Knowle, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1060–":"1060–Décédée","1060–Male":"1060–Décédé","1085–1129":"1085–1129","1060–Female":"1060–Décédée","1129":"1129","1085":"1085","1060":"1060","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni",